16:47.530 --> 16:49.198
think that I run "The New York Times"?

16:49.199 --> 16:51.167
I can't help you with this.

16:51.168 --> 16:53.336
Sorry to hear that. What
would you suggest I do?

16:53.337 --> 16:55.704
Take your pick. I got 23 parties,

16:55.705 --> 16:58.107
37 new restaurants, 12 new discos.

16:58.108 --> 17:01.110
Listen, I can't get anyone
here to write another article.

17:01.111 --> 17:02.878
I've talked to half a dozen reporters

17:02.879 --> 17:04.378
and the guy who worked on the first piece.

17:04.380 --> 17:06.815
"Mr. Leather"? Yeah, no.

17:06.816 --> 17:09.550
No one here will write
about it and I can't.

17:09.551 --> 17:11.819
Look, we're very compartmentalized.

17:11.820 --> 17:14.455
You wouldn't want science to
write about sweaters, would you?

17:14.457 --> 17:16.257
It's a very peculiar
feeling having to go out

17:16.258 --> 17:18.425
and seek support from a
straight world for something gay.

17:20.262 --> 17:22.030
(Whispering) I wouldn't know about that.

17:22.031 --> 17:24.432
I just write about gay
designers and gay discos

17:24.433 --> 17:26.767
and gay chefs and gay
models and gay rock stars

17:26.768 --> 17:28.936
and gay celebrities and gay everything.

17:28.937 --> 17:31.606
