39:10.097 --> 39:12.031
I'm all right.

39:12.032 --> 39:14.334
And if I'm not, I don't wanna
know because no one will hire me,

39:20.040 --> 39:23.510
and haven't lostork any weight.

39:23.511 --> 39:25.812
I can still cover it up.

39:30.250 --> 39:32.951
- I told you not to tell him.
- Sorry.

39:37.957 --> 39:39.992
Already afraid to kiss me?

39:39.993 --> 39:43.829
That's not true.

39:43.830 --> 39:46.531
It's okay. I'm afraid to let you.

40:00.913 --> 40:02.781
I love you.

40:08.854 --> 40:11.889
I'll walk him down.

40:11.890 --> 40:16.127
<i>(Door opens, closes)</i>

40:18.096 --> 40:21.465
Okay, he's the third guy I've been with.

40:21.466 --> 40:24.935
Reinhardt, Craig, and I
don't know what I'll do

40:24.936 --> 40:26.437
if Albert has this.

40:26.438 --> 40:28.939
You're gonna fight.

40:28.940 --> 40:32.409
We'll fight together.

40:32.410 --> 40:34.945
You're my best friend, Ned Weeks.

40:34.946 --> 40:38.949
You're my best friend and I've
never met anyone like you before.

40:38.950 --> 40:40.250
What do you mean, like me?

40:40.251 --> 40:42.085
Like you, meaning...

40:44.421 --> 40:46.056
where I'm from, I... I mean...

40:46.057 --> 40:48.992
I didn't even see a Jew
until I was in the Army,

40:49.994 --> 40:52.495
let alone a man that was

40:52.496 --> 40:54.497
smart,

40:54.498 --> 40:56.599
funny...

41:01.271 --> 41:03.239
decently good-looking.

41:05.576 --> 41:07.009
My friends stopped hanging out with me

41:07.010 --> 41:09.511
because they say I depress them.

41:11.147 --> 41:13.015
So be it.

41:18.721 --> 41:21.690
And you...

41:21.691 --> 41:23.259
<i>you don't look that Jewish.</i>

41:23.260 --> 41:24.593
Well, you don't look gay,

41:24.594 --> 41:27.061
so I guess we can both
pass for white people.

41:35.772 --> 41:38.774
I love Albert.

41:38.775 --> 41:40.442
Bruce, look at me.

41:40.443 --> 41:42.510
I love him.

41:42.511 --> 41:45.380
Albert's gonna make it.

41:48.117 --> 41:50.618
What if he doesn't?

41:53.956 --> 41:56.024
Let's get you home.

41:59.795 --> 42:02.195
<i>(Distant siren wailing)</i>

42:04.800 --> 42:06.801
(retching)

42:10.038 --> 42:13.206
- I'm a mess.
- Yeah.

42:13.207 --> 42:15.642
(Panting)

42:23.884 --> 42:25.852
(Water splashing)

42:26.854 --> 42:29.489
- Classy moment.
- Yeah.

42:47.475 --> 42:48.975
(Thumps)

42:49.977 --> 42:52.211
- I'm all right.
- Okay.

43:04.524 --> 43:06.057
When I finally get you where I want you,

43:06.058 --> 43:08.159
I don't want you anymore.

43:10.530 --> 43:13.031
Hey, Bruce, I'm in love too.

43:18.070 --> 43:20.472
Hey.

43:26.745 --> 43:29.647
Holy shit!

43:29.648 --> 43:31.416
Queen control.

43:31.417 --> 43:33.784
Really works when it wants to.

43:39.124 --> 43:41.125
(Voices overlapping)

43:43.161 --> 43:45.429
Oh, hey, Felix. This is Dick Lombardo.

43:45.430 --> 43:46.931
- Hi.
- Finally got us someone on our board

43:46.932 --> 43:48.566
who isn't a disco dummy.

43:48.567 --> 43:50.568
Well... maybe tonight.

43:50.569 --> 43:52.537
- I'll see ya.
- Felix: Nice to meet ya.

43:52.538 --> 43:54.138
Ned: Come on.

43:57.308 --> 43:58.542
<i>♪ ...and so you're back</i>

43:58.543 --> 44:00.610
<i>♪ From outer space</i>

44:00.611 --> 44:02.679
<i>♪ I just walked in to find you here ♪</i>

44:02.680 --> 44:04.648
<i>♪ With that sad look upon your face ♪</i>

44:04.649 --> 44:06.750
<i>♪ I should have changed
that stupid lock ♪</i>

44:06.751 --> 44:09.053
<i>♪ I should have made
you leave your key ♪</i>

44:09.054 --> 44:11.120
<i>♪ If I had known for just one second ♪</i>

44:11.121 --> 44:12.923
<i>♪ You'd be back to bother me ♪</i>

44:12.924 --> 44:15.025
<i>♪ Go on, now go</i>

44:15.026 --> 44:17.193
<i>♪ Walk out the door</i>

44:17.194 --> 44:19.228
<i>♪ Just turn around now</i>

44:19.229 --> 44:22.231
<i>♪ 'Cause you're not welcome anymore ♪</i>

44:22.232 --> 44:25.468
<i>♪ Weren't you the one who
tried to hurt me with goodbye? ♪</i>

44:25.469 --> 44:27.603
<i>♪ Did you think I'd crumble? ♪</i>

44:27.604 --> 44:29.672
<i>♪ Did you think I'd lay down and die? ♪</i>

44:29.673 --> 44:31.474
<i>♪ Oh, no, not I</i>

44:31.475 --> 44:33.909
<i>- ♪ I will survive...
- (Taps)</i>

44:33.910 --> 44:36.011
<i>- ♪ Oh, as long as...
- (Music stops)</i>

44:36.012 --> 44:38.281
(Groaning)

44:38.282 --> 44:40.416
We are all so happy you joined us tonight!

44:40.417 --> 44:42.218
(Applause, cheering)

44:42.219 --> 44:44.386
We are proving that we are more than just

44:44.387 --> 44:47.489
looks, brains, talent and heart.

44:47.490 --> 44:51.894
<i>Together we raised more than
any gay group ever in this city.</i>

44:53.930 --> 44:56.131
And I wanna call over

44:56.132 --> 44:58.834
Mr. Ned Weeks.

44:58.835 --> 45:00.268
(Cheering continues)

45:00.269 --> 45:02.504
Don't be shy.

45:09.112 --> 45:10.545
We did it!

45:10.546 --> 45:13.748
We will now reveal just
how much we raised together.

45:13.749 --> 45:15.950
In three, two, one...

45:15.951 --> 45:18.820
(Together) $53,000!

45:18.821 --> 45:20.922
(Cheering resumes)

45:35.570 --> 45:38.439
Gay Men's Health Crisis, come on up.

45:38.440 --> 45:40.541
<i>Felix, honey, come on up, please. Come up.</i>

45:40.542 --> 45:42.909
I love you.

45:45.780 --> 45:47.114
Let's dance!

45:47.115 --> 45:49.416
<i>(Music resumes) ♪ Just turn around now</i>

45:49.417 --> 45:52.119
<i>♪ 'Cause you're not welcome anymore ♪</i>

45:52.120 --> 45:55.588
<i>♪ Weren't you the one who tried
to break me with goodbye? ♪</i>

45:55.589 --> 45:57.590
<i>♪ Did you think I'd crumble? ♪</i>

45:57.591 --> 45:59.660
<i>♪ Did you think I'd lay down and die? ♪</i>

45:59.661 --> 46:01.494
<i>♪ Oh, no, not I</i>

46:01.495 --> 46:03.664
<i>♪ I will survive</i>

46:03.665 --> 46:06.299
<i>♪ Oh, as long as I know how to love ♪</i>

46:06.300 --> 46:08.401
<i>♪ I know I'll stay alive... ♪</i>

46:10.070 --> 46:12.071
(playing softly)

46:15.309 --> 46:19.045
<i>♪ Someday he'll come along</i>

46:19.046 --> 46:22.515
♪ The man I love

46:22.516 --> 46:26.418
♪ And he'll be big and strong ♪

46:26.419 --> 46:30.122
♪ The man I love

46:30.123 --> 46:33.893
♪ And when he comes my way ♪

46:33.894 --> 46:36.228
♪ I'll do my best

46:36.229 --> 46:43.402
♪ To make him stay

46:45.405 --> 46:49.074
<i>♪ He'll look at me and smile ♪</i>

46:49.075 --> 46:52.611
<i>♪ I'll understand</i>

46:52.612 --> 46:56.114
<i>♪ And in a little while</i>

46:56.115 --> 46:59.684
<i>♪ He'll take my hand</i>

46:59.685 --> 47:03.321
<i>♪ And though it seems absurd ♪</i>

47:03.322 --> 47:11.763
<i>♪ I know we both won't say a word ♪</i>

47:14.065 --> 47:19.069
<i>♪ Maybe I shall meet him Sunday ♪</i>

47:19.070 --> 47:22.940
<i>♪ Maybe Monday</i>

47:22.941 --> 47:27.111
<i>♪ Maybe not</i>

47:28.714 --> 47:31.849
♪ Still I'm sure to meet him... ♪

47:31.850 --> 47:35.452
Imagine if we had this when we were young.

47:35.453 --> 47:37.087
No fear, no shame.

47:40.959 --> 47:46.996
All I was imagining
all those years was you.

47:46.997 --> 47:50.967
<i>♪ He'll build a little home ♪</i>

47:50.968 --> 47:54.704
<i>♪ Just meant for two</i>

47:54.705 --> 47:58.275
<i>♪ From which I'll never roam ♪</i>

47:58.276 --> 48:01.811
<i>♪ Who would, would you?</i>

48:01.812 --> 48:06.149
<i>♪ And so all else above</i>

48:06.150 --> 48:09.752
<i>♪ I'm waiting for the man... ♪</i>

48:09.753 --> 48:13.055
Felix Turner, would you
like to move in with me?

48:13.056 --> 48:14.657
Yes.

48:14.658 --> 48:16.092
- Yes?
- Yesterday.

48:16.093 --> 48:18.094
Yes? Yes!

48:18.095 --> 48:23.098
<i>- Yes! Yes!
- ♪ And so all else above...</i>

48:23.099 --> 48:25.401
(onlookers cheering)

48:25.402 --> 48:28.837
<i>♪ I'm waiting for</i>

48:28.838 --> 48:33.008
<i>♪ The man</i>

48:33.009 --> 48:38.280
<i>♪ I love.</i>

48:46.622 --> 48:48.990
<i>Ned: "We are all walking time bombs</i>

48:48.991 --> 48:51.326
<i>waiting for whatever it is to set us off."</i>

48:51.327 --> 48:53.695
(Gasping)

48:58.200 --> 48:58.979
C'mon, we're almost there.

48:58.980 --> 49:01.003
<i>- Ned: "If this article doesn't
scare the shit out of you,</i>

49:01.470 --> 49:04.138
<i>gay men may have no future here on Earth.</i>

49:04.139 --> 49:07.141
<i>Our continued existence depends
on just how angry you can get."</i>

49:07.142 --> 49:09.343
<i>- (Bell pings)
- (Banging on door)</i>

49:11.746 --> 49:13.166
They turned us away from
four emergency rooms.

49:13.167 --> 49:14.037
Come in!

49:14.038 --> 49:15.816
I think he's lost his mind.

49:15.817 --> 49:16.715
D, where can I take him?

49:16.716 --> 49:18.239
Put him on the couch there. I'll call Emma.

49:18.240 --> 49:21.788
- God damn it!
- I'll get some water.

49:21.789 --> 49:23.390
<i>Ned: How long has he been like this?</i>

49:23.391 --> 49:25.659
- A couple hours.
- (Gasping)

49:27.662 --> 49:30.929
Well, I'm glad you asked me that question.

49:30.930 --> 49:33.632
What do I think? I know that the government

49:33.633 --> 49:37.236
is intentionally ignoring this epidemic.

49:37.237 --> 49:40.339
You're accusing the
government of the United States

49:40.340 --> 49:43.609
of a conspiracy to murder all gay men?

49:48.982 --> 49:51.350
Yes. Yes, you can say that.

49:51.351 --> 49:53.385
Yes, Sarabeth, I am. Yes.

49:53.386 --> 49:56.088
That is a powerful accusation.

49:56.089 --> 49:58.790
This is an epidemic and it's being ignored

49:58.791 --> 50:00.292
by the United States government.

50:00.293 --> 50:02.294
- Intentionally?
- Intentionally being ignored.

50:02.295 --> 50:04.295
This is a national emergency.

50:04.296 --> 50:06.130
This is an epidemic. It's a plague.

50:06.131 --> 50:09.166
You can't go on national TV and
accuse the government of murder, Ned.

50:09.167 --> 50:11.969
- Why not?
- Because one day we're gonna get money,

50:11.970 --> 50:13.389
research grants.

50:13.390 --> 50:15.306
Congress still hasn't appropriated a dime.

50:15.307 --> 50:16.941
The mayor's still... on and on!

50:16.942 --> 50:20.211
Ned, when you go public, you have no
right to speak for this organization

50:20.212 --> 50:24.382
unless we have approved what
you have to say in advance.

50:24.383 --> 50:26.984
You know, in point of fact, you aren't
even an officer of this organization

50:26.985 --> 50:29.186
<i>and you shouldn't be
speaking for us at all.</i>

50:29.187 --> 50:32.589
<i>Well, thank you for
sharing that with me, Dick.</i>

50:35.260 --> 50:37.594
<i>(Theme music playing)</i>

50:45.837 --> 50:47.571
Why do you think the city has been so slow

50:47.572 --> 50:50.507
to acknowledge and deal
with this emergency?

50:50.508 --> 50:52.643
Well, you're implying that
the city has recognized

50:52.644 --> 50:55.145
and acknowledged this
emergency, Malcolm. It has not.

50:55.146 --> 50:57.047
Why not, do you think?

50:57.048 --> 50:59.282
Because the mayor's gay
and he's scared shitless

50:59.283 --> 51:00.984
out of his panties it'll blow his cover.

51:00.985 --> 51:02.552
<i>- (Object clatters)
- What?</i>

51:02.553 --> 51:04.154
<i>- Man: Take it off, get it off.
- Are we still rolling?</i>

51:04.155 --> 51:05.888
<i>(Tone beeps)</i>

51:05.889 --> 51:07.523
You can't tell me what to say
when I'm speaking for myself.

51:07.524 --> 51:09.359
Bullshit. They all know you're one of us.

51:09.360 --> 51:10.960
It is totally and politically incorrect

51:10.961 --> 51:13.429
to call someone gay who does
not self-identify as being gay.

51:13.430 --> 51:15.064
I know it's been that way forever,

51:15.065 --> 51:17.433
but something different is
going on here now. We're dying.

51:17.434 --> 51:19.234
The mayor, he's a personal friend of yours.

51:19.235 --> 51:21.070
You want him to appoint you a judge.

51:21.071 --> 51:23.272
Do you have a little conflict
of interest going on here?

51:23.273 --> 51:24.907
- I told you I sent him a memo.
- When?

51:24.908 --> 51:26.408
- Through channels.
- When?

51:26.409 --> 51:28.277
- He'll answer me.
- When?!

51:28.278 --> 51:30.612
<i>There's 110 new cases this month!</i>

51:30.613 --> 51:33.182
Still no meeting with our gay mayor.

51:33.183 --> 51:35.284
No meeting with his gay assistant.

51:38.855 --> 51:41.123
What? Do I embarrass you, Bruce?

51:41.124 --> 51:43.458
Yes. You do.

51:43.459 --> 51:44.726
You get more with honey
than with vinegar, babe.

51:44.727 --> 51:46.127
God, no one's told me that one, Tommy.

51:46.128 --> 51:48.229
No, obviously, they haven't.

51:48.230 --> 51:49.965
I never believed that bullshit, anyway.

51:49.966 --> 51:51.967
We are in over our heads with
the patients we're trying to help.

51:51.968 --> 51:55.103
Tommy, will you please read
this report out loud for Ned?

51:55.104 --> 51:59.073
<i>Tommy: We have trained 25 crisis counselors</i>

51:59.074 --> 52:01.909
to help the newly diagnosed in
whatever needs that they might have.

52:01.910 --> 52:05.546
We have 12 group leaders who
meet with these counselors

52:05.547 --> 52:07.648
at least once a week to
go over their clients.

52:07.649 --> 52:09.450
<i>There are now 17 volunteer social workers,</i>

52:09.451 --> 52:12.020
psychologists and/or psychiatrists.

52:12.021 --> 52:13.654
We helped draw up 75 wills last...

52:13.655 --> 52:16.423
75, Bruce!

52:16.424 --> 52:18.125
You used to be a fighter once.

52:18.126 --> 52:21.061
- Did you like being in the Green Berets?
- Yes. I loved it.

52:21.062 --> 52:23.096
Have you completely forgotten how to fight?

52:23.097 --> 52:25.699
Don't tell me how to fight. I
just fight differently than you.

52:25.700 --> 52:27.668
- I haven't seen your way yet.
- No?

52:27.669 --> 52:30.404
Bruce... Albert may be dying.

52:30.405 --> 52:33.306
You son of a bitch! You
say another word about him!

52:33.307 --> 52:36.043
Relax.

52:36.044 --> 52:37.944
And you.

52:37.945 --> 52:40.514
You have no right being on this board

52:40.515 --> 52:42.582
<i>unless you put pressure
on your friend the mayor.</i>

52:42.583 --> 52:45.618
That's why I asked you to join us
in the first place and you know it.

52:52.927 --> 52:55.161
(Panting)

52:57.598 --> 52:59.699
- Ben: No, no, I'm not gonna do that.
- Why not?

52:59.700 --> 53:01.434
No, you got your free
legal work from my firm.

53:01.435 --> 53:03.202
I'm not gonna be on
your board of directors.

53:03.203 --> 53:05.571
It's only for the stationery.
You don't have to do a thing.

53:05.572 --> 53:08.641
That is just an evasion. If you
thought this was a straight disease...

53:08.642 --> 53:09.919
It's got nothing to do with you being gay.

53:09.920 --> 53:11.379
What else does it have to do with?

53:12.011 --> 53:13.379
One of these days, I'm
gonna get you to agree

53:13.380 --> 53:15.581
that over 20 million men
and women in this country

53:15.582 --> 53:18.384
don't require the
services of a psychiatrist.

53:18.385 --> 53:19.685
Look, try to understand.

53:19.686 --> 53:21.887
You know, I read stuff, I see TV.

53:21.888 --> 53:23.889
Guys in leather and chains.

53:23.890 --> 53:25.657
Dresses, high heels.

53:25.658 --> 53:27.492
I say to myself, "This isn't Ned."

53:27.493 --> 53:30.295
You know the media always
dramatizes the most extreme.

53:30.296 --> 53:32.497
You guys have a dreadful image problem.

53:32.498 --> 53:33.999
That's why it's so important

53:34.000 --> 53:35.433
to have people like you supporting us.

53:35.434 --> 53:37.135
You already have your dignity.

53:37.136 --> 53:39.737
Ben: We better get to lunch.
I've got an important meeting.

53:39.738 --> 53:41.939
Do you? How important?

53:41.940 --> 53:43.575
I'm asking for your support.

53:43.576 --> 53:46.177
In every area I consider
important, you have my support.

53:46.178 --> 53:49.147
<i>The only area that I consider important</i>

53:49.148 --> 53:52.083
I don't have your support at all.

53:52.084 --> 53:54.152
In some place deep down inside you,

53:54.153 --> 53:55.419
you still think I'm sick, don't you?

53:55.420 --> 53:57.187
I think you've adjusted
to life pretty well.

53:57.188 --> 54:00.591
- All things considered.
- I saw how unhappy you were.

54:00.592 --> 54:02.192
So were you!

54:02.193 --> 54:05.930
You wound up going to shrinks,
too. We grew up side by side.

54:05.931 --> 54:08.699
We both felt the same about Mom and Pop.

54:08.700 --> 54:13.069
I'll agree to the fact that I have
any number of awful character traits,

54:13.070 --> 54:16.906
<i>but not to the fact that whatever
awful things they did to us</i>

54:16.907 --> 54:20.744
made me sick and gay while you
stayed straight and healthy.

54:20.745 --> 54:22.846
We don't all react the
same way to the thing.

54:22.847 --> 54:25.215
So you became a lawyer
and I became a writer.

